data.name: Formal analysis
data.desc: Application of statistical, mathematical, computational, or other formal techniques to analyze or synthesize study data.

data.name: Investigation
data.desc: Conducting a research and investigation process, specifically performing the experiments, or data/evidence collection.

data.name: Methodology
data.desc: Development or design of methodology; creation of models.

data.name: Project administration
data.desc: Management and coordination responsibility for the research activity planning and execution.

data.name: Resources
data.desc: Provision of study materials, reagents, materials, patients, laboratory samples, animals, instrumentation, computing resources, or other analysis tools.

data.name: Data curation
data.desc: Management activities to annotate (produce metadata), scrub data and maintain research data (including software code, where it is necessary for interpreting the data itself) for initial use and later re-use.

data.name: Writing – original draft
data.desc: Preparation, creation and/or presentation of the published work, specifically writing the initial draft (including substantive translation).

data.name: Writing – review & editing
data.desc: Preparation, creation and/or presentation of the published work by those from the original research group, specifically critical review, commentary or revision – including pre- or post-publication stages.

data.name: Validation
data.desc: Verification, whether as a part of the activity or separate, of the overall replication/reproducibility of results/experiments and other research outputs.

data.name: Conceptualization
data.desc: Ideas; formulation or evolution of overarching research goals and aims.

data.name: Funding acquisition
data.desc: Acquisition of the financial support for the project leading to this publication.

data.name: Supervision
data.desc: Oversight and leadership responsibility for the research activity planning and execution, including mentorship external to the core team.

data.name: Software
data.desc: Programming, software development; designing computer programs; implementation of the computer code and supporting algorithms; testing of existing code components.

data.name: Visualization
data.desc: Preparation, creation and/or presentation of the published work, specifically visualization/data presentation.
